<DOC><DOCNO> AP890801-0006 </DOCNO><FILEID>AP-NR-08-01-89 0052EDT</FILEID><FIRST>r i PM-Hostages-Chronology     08-01 1190</FIRST><SECOND>PM-Hostages-Chronology,1247</SECOND><HEAD>Five Years of Abductions, Threats, Death</HEAD><HEAD>With PM-Hostages Bjt</HEAD><BYLINE>By The Associated Press</BYLINE><TEXT>   Here is a chronology of events in the holding of American kidnapvictims in Lebanon:</TEXT><NOTE>1984</NOTE><TEXT>   FEB. 10 _ Frank Regier, engineering professor at AmericanUniversity in Beirut, abducted near west Beirut campus.   FEB. 26 _ U.S. Marines withdraw from Beirut.   MARCH 7 _ Jeremy Levin, Beirut chief for U.S. Cable NewsNetwork, kidnapped as walks to work in west Beirut.   MARCH 16 _ Gunmen abduct U.S. Embassy political officer WilliamBuckley outside home in west Beirut.   APRIL 15 _ Regier and kidnapped Frenchman Christian Joubert gainfreedom from unidentified captors. Shiite Amal militia claimscredit for rescue.   MAY 8 _ Kidnappers overpower American Presbyterian pastorBenjamin Weir on west Beirut street and carry him off.   MAY 9 _ Anonymous caller to French news agency claims IslamicJihad, shadowy anti-Western group of Shiite Moslems, holds Buckley,Levin, Weir.   SEPT. 20 _ Car-bomb at U.S. Embassy annex in east Beirut killsat least 14 people, including two Americans.   DEC. 3 _ American University librarian Peter Kilburn fails toreport to work. It is later claimed he was kidnapped by IslamicJihad.</TEXT><NOTE>1985</NOTE><TEXT>   JAN. 8 _ Rev. Lawrence Martin Jenco, Roman Catholic priest,abducted from car by gunmen in Beirut. Anonymous caller later saysJenco and four other missing Americans will be freed ``if allAmericans leave Lebanon.''   FEB. 14 _ Levin gains freedom in Lebanon and is turned over toU.S. authorities by Syria. He says he escaped; Islamic Jihad saysit freed him.   MARCH 16 _ Terry Anderson, chief Mideast correspondent of TheAssociated Press, abducted on Beirut street. Caller says IslamicJihad kidnapped Anderson.   MAY 16 _ Islamic Jihad warns of ``catastrophic consequences''for hostages if Kuwait does not free 17 Islamic Jihad comradesjailed in Kuwait for December 1983 bombing of U.S. and Frenchembassies there.   MAY 28 _ Gunmen kidnap David P. Jacobsen, American director ofAmerican University Hospital, as he walks to work in west Beirut.   MAY 30 _ Caller claiming to represent Islamic Jihad says groupkilled Denis Hill, British teacher of English at AmericanUniversity who disappeared May 27 and was later found shot in head,and holds Jacobsen.   JUNE 10 _ Gunmen on Beirut airport highway kidnap AmericanThomas Sutherland, acting agriculture dean at American University.   JUNE 30 _ Lebanese terrorists free last 39 hostages from TWAjetliner they hijacked and forced to Beirut.   SEPT. 9 _ President Reagan announces Weir has been freed after16 months in captivity.   OCT. 4 _ Islamic Jihad claims it has killed Buckley inretaliation for Israeli air raid on PLO headquarters in Tunisia. Itlater releases photographs it says show Buckley's body, and offersto turn body over to United Nations if Israel releases 100Palestinian prisoners.   NOV. 8 _ In open letter, four captive Americans _ Anderson,Jenco, Jacobsen and Sutherland _ call on Reagan to ``have mercy''and negotiate with kidnappers.   NOV. 13 _ Church of England official Terry Waite beginsmediation to try to gain hostages' release, shuttling among Beirut,Washington and European capitals.</TEXT><NOTE>1986</NOTE><TEXT>   APRIL 17 _ Kilburn and two other hostages, British educatorsLeigh Douglas and Philip Padfield, found shot to death east ofBeirut. Note says Arab Revolutionary Cells killed them inretaliation for April 15 U.S. air attack on Libya.   APRIL 23 _ Revolutionary Organization of Socialist Moslems saysit has killed kidnapped British journalist Alec Collett inretaliation for British complicity in U.S. attack on Libya.Videotape purporting to show him hanged is made public. Collett, onassignment with U.N. relief agency, was kidnapped March 25, 1985.   JULY 26 _ Jenco freed. He later delivers confidential message toReagan from kidnappers.   SEPT. 9 _ American educator Frank Herbert Reed kidnapped in westBeirut.   SEPT. 12 _ American University accountant Joseph Cicippioabducted on west Beirut campus. Callers claim responsibility forboth Reed and Cicippio abductions in name of two groups _Resurrection Cells, and Arab Revolutionary Cells-Omar MoukhtarForces. Later, Revolutionary Justice Organization claimsresponsibility for kidnapping of Cicippio.   OCT. 21 _ Revolutionary Justice Organization claims to havekidnapped another American in Beirut, writer Edward Austin Tracy.   NOV. 2 _ Jacobsen is released in Beirut. Islamic Jihad says U.S.must continue pursuing ``current approaches'' to win freedom forother hostages.   NOV. 3 _ First reports surface that U.S., beginning in 1985,arranged arms shipments to Iran in exchange for hostage releases.   NOV. 28 _ Iran's Parliament speaker, Hashemi Rafsanjani, saysTehran government will help free hostages if Washington returnsfrozen Iranian assets in U.S. Talks on returning frozen U.S. assetsto Iran are later suspended.</TEXT><NOTE>1987</NOTE><TEXT>   JAN. 20 _ Vice President George Bush says hostage Buckley diedafter torture. Anglican Church mediator Waite drops from sight inBeirut. Unconfirmed reports say he is captive of extremists.   JAN. 24 _ Three Americans _ Jesse Jonathan Turner, Alann Steenand Robert Polhill _ and Indian Mithileshwar Singh, all facultymembers of Beirut University College, are kidnapped from thecampus. Group calling itself Islamic Jihad for Liberation ofPalestine claims responsibility.   FEB. 9 _ Islamic Jihad for Liberation of Palestine, threateningto kill Turner, Steen, Polhill and Singh unless Israel frees Arabprisoners, ``postpones'' the act just before deadline.   MARCH 26 _ Videotape released in which Turner says fellowhostage Steen is ill and dying, and urging release of Arabprisoners in Israel in exchange for hostages' freedom.   JUNE 17 _ American journalist Charles Glass, on leave from hisjob at ABC News, is kidnapped in west Beirut. He escapes two monthslater.   DEC. 24 _ Kidnappers issue videotape of Anderson in which heappeals to President Reagan to win the hostages' release, saying,``There is a limit for how long we can last.''</TEXT><NOTE>1988</NOTE><TEXT>   FEB. 17 _ U.S. Marine Lt. Col. William R. Higgins, chief ofobserver unit attached to U.N. peacekeeping force in Lebanon, isseized by gunmen on southern Lebanese highway. The Organization ofOppressed on Earth claims to hold him and demands release ofprisoners held by Israel.   MAY 4 _ The last three French hostages in Lebanon are set free.They say a fourth French hostage, Michel Seurat, died in captivity.French Premier Michel Rocard later says France will re-establishdiplomatic relations with Iran.   OCT. 3 _ Indian professor Mithileshwar Singh is freed.</TEXT><NOTE>1989</NOTE><TEXT>   MARCH 3 _ Lebanon's most influential Shiite Moslem cleric, SheikMohammed Hussein Fadlallah, says the foreign hostages should befreed because ``abduction is wrong.''   JUNE 8 _ Iran's Parliament speaker, Hashemi Rafsanjani, saysIran will help free American hostages in Lebanon if the UnitedStates tries to win freedom for Iranians held by Christian forcesin Lebanon.   JULY 28 _ Israeli commandos abduct Sheik Abdul Karim Obeid, aShiite Moslem cleric and a leader of the Hezbollah, from his homein south Lebanon.   JULY 30 _ Organization of the Oppressed on Earth threatens tokill Higgins if Obeid is not freed.   JULY 31 _ Organization of the Oppressed on Earth says Higginshas been killed, releases videotape purporting to show his hangedbody. Revolutionary Justice Organization threatens to kill Cicippioif Shiite cleric is not freed.</TEXT></DOC>